          <mxGeometry height="80" width="160" x="1290" y="195" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="4DyDUN3vrFLzL9egiClx-13" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#f0a30a;fontColor=#000000;strokeColor=#BD7000;" value="Does the acquisition agent really participate on an assets market? How are prefrences of the assets (busy/free) modeled? NEAT!" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="80" width="160" x="-160" y="800" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="4DyDUN3vrFLzL9egiClx-14" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#f0a30a;fontColor=#000000;strokeColor=#BD7000;" value="How to avoid infinite loops between logistician and asset portfolio manager? Procure device, not available, procure, not available, etc?" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="80" width="160" x="-160" y="920" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="4DyDUN3vrFLzL9egiClx-15" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#f0a30a;fontColor=#000000;strokeColor=#BD7000;" value="CaCSM produces an abstract intent, CaCSM does not have ORACS. But, its supposed to have at list the inventary of devices (what worked in the past), right? Otherwise it will be impossible to reconcile with the Logisticiam and Asset Portfolio Manager ORACS. What happends when the history is changed? Like new devices where added? What worked on the past might drift from what will work now. Continuous learning?" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="240" width="160" x="-160" y="520" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="4DyDUN3vrFLzL9egiClx-18" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#f0a30a;fontColor=#000000;strokeColor=#BD7000;" value="1. No optimality ideas. Learning yes, but no optimality.&lt;div&gt;2. A giant adaptable lookup table: what worked on the past, lets solve it again in the same way.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;3. CaCSM is not a reasoning engine, is a match engine. In this sense, the system will not be able to solve situations that never saw before. So, we will have self-healing only on previously healed conditions.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;4. Lack of generalization over the learningWorks only in the network that was learned&quot;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="280" width="160" x="1920" y="-400" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="4DyDUN3vrFLzL9egiClx-19" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#f0a30a;fontColor=#000000;strokeColor=#BD7000;" value="A cell can hand off authority to a neighbor. This is managed by the Federated Edge Transaction Manager. Is this transfer cell 1 notifies transfer to cloud, cloud terminates cell 1, cloud spawn cell 2 with same config as 1? Or is it really a local cell 1 transfer itself to cell 2 over local network without cloud involvement?" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="180" width="160" x="1630" y="1550" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="4DyDUN3vrFLzL9egiClx-20" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#f0a30a;fontColor=#000000;strokeColor=#BD7000;" value="How to avoid infinite loops between logistician and asset portfolio manager? Procure device, not available, procure, not available, etc?" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="80" width="160" x="-160" y="1040" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
